reviews.review_text: Not Good The boys sound lost and out of tune.  This is not enjoyable to listen to.  The Scarlett/Fire is just off.  The sound quality is decent, so It gets 2 stars but the performance is a 1.

No Way...... This show is 100% pure 1985 GOLD!!!  Both sets are sick, but the second is just outstanding.  Great Scarlet>Fire and the Cryptical >Thats It For the Other One is the mind melter of the decade BUST OUT!  First time since the early 70's, I believe. .... 1st Walkin' Blues in a few years in the first set, too.   Very enjoyable show on all fronts.   Don't skip the  second set.....!! :)
eh on paper it's a great 2nd set but this isn't exactly on par with most of '85... summer '84 Greek run was so superb; this is just... eh.
WOW!!! Excellent rendition of Scar-Fire. LOVE IT!! LOve the 85' sound.. =)

Rock Solid I'm not sure who could only give this show only a couple of stars.  Have you had your hearing checked lately?  Mine may not be the best either after so many live shows.  But, other than a few sound flaws at the beginning and the hilarious Jerry gaf of the lyrics in Big RR Blues:), this show was a ripper!!  The Scarlet/Fire, while not quite as in your face as some, has an amazing tight jazziness to the scarlet and the fire builds to a very powerful crescendo.  Then to bust out the Cryptical and wipe the faces off of all in attendance---ROCK SOLID!!

I have heard stories about the fog rolling into the bay with the sun setting a brilliant red to the fog.  Wish I could have attended this whole run!  Didn't make it to the greek until the following year.

Second Set I love this 2nd set! All is wonderful to hear, but the Scarlet/Fire and TOO are what really keep me coming back. GDTRFB also. And the Brokedown. 

This is one of the first tapes I had as a youngster. It's still one of the best!
My first GDTRFB This was so much fun.  Haven't listened in years.  I remember my joy hearing GDTR out of space.  I left floating I was so happy.
